{{Infobox football biography | name = Diego Michiels | image = | fullname = Diego Muhammad bin Robbie Michiels | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|08|08}} | birth_place = [[Deventer]], [[Netherlands]] | height = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|abbr=on}} | currentclub = [[Pusamania Borneo F.C.|Borneo F.C.]] | clubnumber = 24 | youthyears1 = 2006 | youthclubs1 = DVV RDC | youthyears2 = 2007–2009 | youthclubs2 = [[Go Ahead Eagles]] | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | years1 = 2009–2011 | clubs1 = [[Go Ahead Eagles]] | caps1 = 17 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2011–2013 | clubs2 = [[Pelita Jaya FC|Pelita Jaya]] | caps2 = 45 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2012 | clubs3 = → [[Arema FC|Arema Indonesia]] (loan) | caps3 = 18 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2013–2014 | clubs4 = [[Sriwijaya F.C.|Sriwijaya]] | caps4 = 32 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2014–2015 | clubs5 = [[Mitra Kukar F.C.|Mitra Kukar]] | caps5 = 25 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2015– | clubs6 = [[Pusamania Borneo F.C.|Borneo F.C.]] | caps6 = 59 | goals6 = 5
| nationalyears1 = 2011–2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Indonesia national under-23 football team|Indonesia U-23]] | nationalcaps1 = 16 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2012– | nationalteam2 = [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]] | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | medaltemplates = {{medalTeam|Indonesia U-23}} {{MedalCompetition|[[Southeast Asian Games]]}} {{medalSilver|[[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011 SEA Games]]|[[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011]]}} {{medalSilver|[[Football at the 2013 Southeast Asian Games|2013 SEA Games]]|[[Football at the 2013 Southeast Asian Games|2013]]}} | pcupdate = 30 November 2018 | ntupdate = 29 March 2014 }} '''Diego Muhammad bin Robbie Michiels''' or '''Diego Michiels''' (born August 8, 1990 in [[Deventer]], [[Netherlands]])<ref name=soccerway>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/diego-michiels/108316/|title=Indonesia - D. Michiels - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|publisher=}}</ref> is an [[Indonesia]]n professional [[Association football|footballer]] who currently plays for [[Pusamania Borneo F.C.|Borneo F.C.]] as a defender in the [[Liga 1 (Indonesia) | Liga 1]]. Diego is of [[Dutch people|Dutch]]-[[Indonesian people|Indonesian]] roots. His father, Robbie Michiels, is from [[Jakarta]]. While his mother, Annet Kloppenburg, is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] citizen.
==International career== In 2011, Diego and [[Joey Suk]] were invited by the Indonesian Football Association to play for the [[Indonesia national under-23 football team]] in Jakarta. According to the newspaper report, he was interested in joining the Indonesian national team, even though he would have to give up his Dutch passport. Along with Joey and Ruben Wuarbanaran, will be able to play for the Indonesia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpnn.com/read/2011/04/07/88923/Paspor-Tiga-Pemain-Naturalisasi-Tuntas-|title=Paspor Tiga Pemain Naturalisasi Tuntas|first=|last=JPNN.com|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut for Indonesia in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] on February 29, 2012.{{citation needed|date=May 2013}}
