'''Jacques Newashish''' (1958) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] film actor, filmmaker, painter, and sculptor.<ref>[http://www.nationnews.ca/streets-story-struggle-healing-redemption/ "Before the Streets: A story of struggle, healing and redemption"]. ''The Nation'', April 15, 2016.</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://dictionnaire.espaceartactuel.com/en/artistes/newashish-jacques-1958/|title=NEWASHISH, Jacques (1958)|website=Dictionnaire historique de la sculpture québécoise au XXe siècle|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-23}}</ref> Newashish is a member of the [[Atikamekw]] nation and is from [[Wemotaci]], [[Quebec]].<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/indigenous-art-destroyed-montreal-1.4243230 "City workers accidentally destroyed artwork dedicated to missing and murdered Indigenous women"]. [[CBC News]], August 11, 2017.</ref> He was born in [[La Tuque, Quebec|La Tuque]], Quebec<ref name=":0" /> where he learned traditional values and ways of living.<ref name=":0" /> His father was a trapper and hunter and the language and culture of the Atikamekw people.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://sacredfireproductions.ca/artist/jacques-newashish/|title=Jacques Newashish|last=|first=|date=|website=Les Productions Feux Sacrés|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> Newashish incorporates elements of Atikamekw culture into his artistic practice and is concerned with the preservation of the Atikamekw language and culture in the community.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ici.radio-canada.ca/info/videos/media-7784571/jacques-newashish-artiste-autochtone-multidisciplinaire|title=Jacques Newashish artiste autochtone multidisciplinaire|last=|first=|date=|website=Radio-Canada|language=fr|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-01-23}}</ref>
As a multidisciplinary artist, Newashish works across a variety of mediums, including sculpture, painting, film, and storytelling.<ref name=":1" /> His work includes [[Installation art|installations]] which frequently use natural materials which reflect Atikamekw culture.<ref name=":1" />
Newashish garnered a [[Canadian Screen Award]] nomination for [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Performance by an Actor in a Supporting Role|Best Supporting Actor]] at the [[5th Canadian Screen Awards]] for his performance in ''[[Before the Streets]] (Avant les rues)''.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/indigenous/indigenous-artists-nominee-2017-csa-1.3939858 "Indigenous talent among 2017 Canadian Screen Award nominees"]. [[CBC News]], September 17, 2017.</ref>
