{{Infobox monarch | name = Sena and Guttika | title = King of Anuradhapura | image = | caption = | reign = 237 BC – 215 BC | coronation = | full name = | predecessor = [[Suratissa of Anuradhapura|Suratissa]] | successor = [[Asela of Anuradhapura|Asela]] | spouse = | issue = | royal house = | dynasty = | father = | mother = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | date of burial = | place of burial = }}
'''Sena and Guttika''' were two [[Tamils|Tamil]] chiefs from [[South India]] who invaded the [[Anuradhapura Kingdom|kingdom of Anuradhapura]] and killed [[Suratissa of Anuradhapura|King Suratissa]]. They reigned from 237 BC to 215 BC. They were originally two traders who came to Sri Lanka to sell horses; however, they killed Surathissa, the king of Anuradhapura, and ruled the kingdom for 22 years. [[Asela of Anuradhapura|King Asela]] defeated them and re-established the kingdom as a [[Sinhalese monarchy]].
